{'project_name': 'Brazil Precision Agriculture Carbon Program', 'project_summary': 'The Brazil Precision Agriculture Carbon Program (BPACP) incentivizes the large-scale adoption of big data-driven precision agriculture in Brazil.

It is a grouped VCS project implemented by a national carbon credit cooperative society (“Carbon Coop”). The project has partnered with multiple stakeholders on a national scale, including soil laboratories, a big data analytics platform, agro-inputs and machinery dealers, local agricultural consultants and soil sampling experts, to connect with farmers and leverage the adoption of precision agriculture.

The carbon project intends to harness data analytics, remote sensing, climate and crop modelling, artificial intelligence, and in-field sensors, to help farmers make data-informed decisions that sustainably increase productivity and crop resilience (adaptation), reduce and remove greenhouse gas emissions (mitigation), and enhance achievement of global food security and national development goals.', 'project_state_province': 'Mato Grosso', 'project_country': 'Brazil', 'project_latitude': -12.54, 'project_longitude': -55.72}

